  <summary date="2020-05-15T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Fair Chance for Small Business Relief Act

This bill prohibits the Small Business Administration from declining to provide or guarantee certain small business loans solely on the basis that an applicant (1) is on probation or parole, (2) is presently subject to a means by which formal criminal charges are brought (e.g., indictment or arraignment), or (3) has been arrested or convicted of any crime.</summary>
